Following the abduction of students of Bethel Baptist School on Monday, some aggrieved women, including parents of the abducted students stormed the ever-busy Kachia Highway in Maraban Rido, blocked the road while protesting over the incessant kidnapping of their wards. This followed the abduction of students on Monday morning from Bethel Baptist High School Kaduna. About 3pm, the women placed logs of wood, preventing people from plying the road. However, a military convoy arrived at the scene at about 3:05pm and opened the road for commuters. Details…….  Source No fewer than 17 kidnapped students of Bethel Baptist High School, Kaduna have returned, Police Public Relations Officer, ASP Mohammed Jalije, has said. The PUNCH had reported that gunmen attacked the Baptist school, located at Damishi town of Chikun Local Government Area in Kaduna State, and took away scores of… In "News" The Speaker Kaduna State House of Assembly, Alhaji Yusuf Zailani has expressed worry that bandits and kidnappers are targeting key sectors of the state. The speaker expressed this concern in a statement signed by his Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Ibrahim Danfulani on Monday. The News Agency of Nigeria… In "News" The spate of insecurity in the country assumed a more dangerous dimension on Monday as Boko Haram insurgents made inroads into Niger State and gunmen killed two students of Greenfield University in Kaduna state. Also on Monday, the Vice-Chancellor of the Federal University of Agriculture, Makurdi, Benue State, Professor Richard… In "News"